This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with action recognition in videos using deep learning techniques. The paper also involves the use of multimodal data, which could place it in the Multimedia (cs.MM) category. The use of a correlation network for learning a pre-trained CNN suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which could place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. Finally, the use of fully connected layers suggests that it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category.
